cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.CL

The paper proposes a deep neural network-based framework for social recommendations, which combines user-item interactions and social network information. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of social network information also suggests the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SOC) and social computing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper focuses on collaborative filtering techniques, which suggests the sub-category of recommender systems (cs.SI).
